Description: Part of a thick-walled calcite vessel: comprising two joined fragments, bearing a partially-erased serekh. The attempted erasure was deliberate, carried out by scratching the surface of the stone.
Curator's comments: For other examples of erased inscriptions of Anedjib, see W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, pl. VI, 10-11; P. Kaplony, 'Mitteilungen der Deutschen Archäologischen Instituts Abteilung Kairo' 20 (Wiesbaden, 1965), 13, abb. 24-25; 18, abb. 32-34. Bibliography: W. M. F. Petrie, 'Royal Tombs of the Earliest Dynasties' I, 20 and pl. VI; P. Kaplony, 'Mitteilungen der Deutschen Archäologischen Instituts Abteilung Kairo' 20 (Wiesbaden, 1965), 13, no. 23.
